data.name: customSqlQuery1.Sql
data.value: SELECT NameBase.ID, PREarn.EmployeeID, PREarn.PRStateID, Sum(HoursWorkedOrUnits) As HoursWorked, Sum(Amount) As Amount, Sum(Amount + IIF(ShortDescr = 'Normal' AND (EarningCode_SYEnumID = 930 OR EarningCode_SYEnumID = 931), OvertimeAmount, IIF(ShortDescr = 'Normal', RegularAmount, OtherAmount))) AS YTDAmount, EarningsClassCode_SYEnumID, IIF(ShortDescr = 'Normal' AND (EarningCode_SYEnumID = 930 OR EarningCode_SYEnumID = 931), 'OVERTIME',IIF(ShortDescr = 'Normal', 'REGULAR', ShortDescr)) AS EarningsTitle, PREarn.CompanyID FROM PREarn INNER JOIN SYEnum On PREarn.EarningsClassCode_SYEnumID = SYEnum.EnumID INNER JOIN PREmployee ON PREmployee.PREmployeeID = PREarn.EmployeeID and PREmployee.CompanyID = PREarn.CompanyID INNER JOIN NameBase ON NameBase.ID = PREmployee.Employee_NameBaseID and PREmployee.CompanyID = @plngCompanyID INNER JOIN (select min(EmployeeID) EmployeeID, min(PRStateID) PRStateID, year(CheckDate) CheckDate, sum(RegularAmount) RegularAmount, sum(OvertimeAmount) OvertimeAmount, SUM(OtherAmount) OtherAmount, CompanyID from PRPaycheckHistory where year(checkdate) = year(@pdteCheckDate) AND CompanyID=@plngCompanyID group by EmployeeID, PRStateID, year(CheckDate), CompanyID ) HIST ON PREarn.EmployeeID=HIST.EmployeeID AND PREarn.PRStateID=HIST.PRStateID and PREarn.CompanyID=HIST.CompanyID GROUP BY NameBase.ID, PREarn.EmployeeID, PREarn.PRStateID, EarningsClassCode_SYEnumID, EarningCode_SYEnumID, ShortDescr,PREarn.CompanyID

data.name: customSqlQuery2.Sql
data.value: SELECT NameBase.ID ,PRT.EmployeeID ,(SELECT TOP 1 A.PRStateID FROM PRTimeHistory A WHERE A.EmployeeID = PRT.EmployeeID AND A.CompanyID = PRT.CompanyID) AS StateID ,(SELECT TOP 1 A.CheckDate FROM PRTimeHistory A WHERE A.EmployeeID = PRT.EmployeeID AND A.CompanyID = PRT.CompanyID) AS CheckDate ,PRT.EarningsClassCode_SYEnumID ,IIF(ShortDescr = 'Normal' AND (EarningCode_SYEnumID = 930 OR EarningCode_SYEnumID = 931), 'OVERTIME',IIF(ShortDescr = 'Normal', 'REGULAR', ShortDescr)) AS EarningsTitle ,Sum(PRT.Amount) AS Amount ,PRT.CompanyID ,NameBase.Number FROM PRTimeHistory AS PRT INNER JOIN SYEnum On PRT.EarningsClassCode_SYEnumID = SYEnum.EnumID INNER JOIN PREmployee ON PREmployee.PREmployeeID = PRT.EmployeeID and PREmployee.CompanyID = PRT.CompanyID INNER JOIN NameBase ON NameBase.ID = PREmployee.Employee_NameBaseID and PREmployee.CompanyID = @plngCompanyID where year(CheckDate)=year(@pdteCheckDate) GROUP BY NameBase.ID, EmployeeID, EarningsClassCode_SYEnumID, PRT.CompanyID, EarningCode_SYEnumID, ShortDescr, NameBase.Number, PRT.PRStateID, year(CheckDate) --ORDER BY NameBase.ID ORDER BY NameBase.Number

SELECT NameBase.ID ,MIN(PRW.EmployeeID) AS EmployeeID ,MIN(PRW.TaxingStateID) AS TaxingStateID ,MIN(FICAAmount) AS FICAAmount ,MIN(MedicareAmount) AS MEDIAmount ,MIN(SITAmount) AS SITAmount ,MIN(FITAmount) AS FITAmount ,SUM(FICAAmount + ISNULL(DEDHIST1.DeductionAmount,0)) as FICAAmountYTD ,SUM(FITAmount + ISNULL(DEDHIST2.DeductionAmount,0)) as FITAmountYTD ,SUM(SITAmount + ISNULL(DEDHIST3.DeductionAmount,0)) as SITAmountYTD ,SUM(MedicareAmount + ISNULL(DEDHIST4.DeductionAmount,0)) as MedicareAmountYTD ,PRW.CompanyID ,NameBase.Number FROM PRWrk2 AS PRW --INNER JOIN SYEnum On PRT.EarningsClassCode_SYEnumID = SYEnum.EnumID INNER JOIN PREmployee ON PREmployee.PREmployeeID = PRW.EmployeeID and PREmployee.CompanyID = PRW.CompanyID INNER JOIN NameBase ON NameBase.ID = PREmployee.Employee_NameBaseID and PREmployee.CompanyID = @plngCompanyID LEFT JOIN ( select min(EmployeeID) EmployeeID, min(PRStateID) PRStateID, year(CheckDate) CheckDate, sum(DeductionAmount) DeductionAmount, min(PRDeductionID) PRDeductionID, min(DeductionCode) DeductionCode, MIN(PRDeductionHistory.CompanyID) CompanyID from PRDeductionHistory inner join PRPaycheckHistory on PRDeduction.ID and PRDeductionHistory.CompanyID=PRDeduction.CompanyID where Year(CheckDate)=year(@pdteCheckDate) AND DeductionCode='1' AND PRDeductionHistory.CompanyID=@plngCompanyID group by EmployeeID, PRStateID, YEAR(CheckDate), PRDeductionID ) DEDHIST1 ON PRW.EmployeeID=DEDHIST1.EmployeeID AND PRW.TaxingStateID=DEDHIST1.PRStateID AND PRW.CompanyID=DEDHIST1.CompanyID LEFT JOIN ( select min(EmployeeID) EmployeeID, min(PRStateID) PRStateID, year(CheckDate) CheckDate, sum(DeductionAmount) DeductionAmount, min(PRDeductionID) PRDeductionID, min(DeductionCode) DeductionCode, MIN(PRDeductionHistory.CompanyID) CompanyID from PRDeductionHistory inner join PRPaycheckHistory on PRPaycheckHistory.PRPaycheckHistoryID=PRDeductionHistory.PRPaycheckHistoryID and PRDeductionHistory.CompanyID=PRPaycheckHistory.CompanyID left join PRDeduction on PRDeductionHistory.PRDeductionID = PRDeduction.ID and PRDeductionHistory.CompanyID=PRDeduction.CompanyID where Year(CheckDate)=year(@pdteCheckDate) AND DeductionCode='2' AND PRDeductionHistory.CompanyID=@plngCompanyID group by EmployeeID, PRStateID, YEAR(CheckDate), PRDeductionID ) DEDHIST2 ON PRW.EmployeeID=DEDHIST1.EmployeeID AND PRW.TaxingStateID=DEDHIST2.PRStateID AND PRW.CompanyID=DEDHIST2.CompanyID LEFT JOIN ( select min(EmployeeID) EmployeeID, min(PRStateID) PRStateID, year(CheckDate) CheckDate, sum(DeductionAmount) DeductionAmount, min(PRDeductionID) PRDeductionID, min(DeductionCode) DeductionCode, MIN(PRDeductionHistory.CompanyID) CompanyID from PRDeductionHistory inner join PRPaycheckHistory on PRPaycheckHistory.PRPaycheckHistoryID=PRDeductionHistory.PRPaycheckHistoryID and PRDeductionHistory.CompanyID=PRPaycheckHistory.CompanyID left join PRDeduction on PRDeductionHistory.PRDeductionID = PRDeduction.ID and PRDeductionHistory.CompanyID=PRDeduction.CompanyID where Year(CheckDate)=year(@pdteCheckDate) AND DeductionCode='3' AND PRDeductionHistory.CompanyID=@plngCompanyID group by EmployeeID, PRStateID, YEAR(CheckDate), PRDeductionID ) DEDHIST3 ON PRW.EmployeeID=DEDHIST3.EmployeeID AND PRW.TaxingStateID=DEDHIST3.PRStateID AND PRW.CompanyID=DEDHIST3.CompanyID LEFT JOIN ( select min(EmployeeID) EmployeeID, min(PRStateID) PRStateID, year(CheckDate) CheckDate, sum(DeductionAmount) DeductionAmount, min(PRDeductionID) PRDeductionID, min(DeductionCode) DeductionCode, MIN(PRDeductionHistory.CompanyID) CompanyID from PRDeductionHistory inner join PRPaycheckHistory on PRPaycheckHistory.PRPaycheckHistoryID=PRDeductionHistory.PRPaycheckHistoryID and PRDeductionHistory.CompanyID=PRPaycheckHistory.CompanyID left join PRDeduction on PRDeductionHistory.PRDeductionID = PRDeduction.ID and PRDeductionHistory.CompanyID=PRDeduction.CompanyID where Year(CheckDate)=year(@pdteCheckDate) AND DeductionCode='4' AND PRDeductionHistory.CompanyID=@plngCompanyID group by EmployeeID, PRStateID, YEAR(CheckDate), PRDeductionID ) DEDHIST4 ON PRW.EmployeeID=DEDHIST4.EmployeeID AND PRW.TaxingStateID=DEDHIST4.PRStateID AND PRW.CompanyID=DEDHIST4.CompanyID
GROUP BY NameBase.ID, PRW.EmployeeID, PRW.CompanyID, NameBase.Number ORDER BY NameBase.Number

data.name: customSqlQuery4.Sql
data.value: SELECT NameBase.ID ,PRDeductionID ,PRD.Heading1 ,Sum(DeductionAmount) as DeductionAmount --,CheckDate ,NameBase.Number FROM PRDeductionHistory PRDH INNER JOIN PRDeduction PRD ON PRDH.PRDeductionID = PRD.ID AND PRDH.CompanyID = PRD.CompanyID INNER JOIN PRPaycheckHistory PRP ON PRDH.PRPaycheckHistoryID = PRP.PRPaycheckHistoryID and PRDH.CompanyID = PRP.CompanyID INNER JOIN PREmployee ON PREmployee.PREmployeeID = PRP.EmployeeID and PREmployee.CompanyID = PRP.CompanyID INNER JOIN NameBase ON NameBase.ID = PREmployee.Employee_NameBaseID and PREmployee.CompanyID = @plngCompanyID --WHERE CheckDate BETWEEN DATEFROMPARTS(YEAR(@pdteCheckDate), 1, 1) --AND DATEFROMPARTS(YEAR(@pdteCheckDate), 12,31) WHERE year(CheckDate)=year(@pdteCheckDate) GROUP BY NameBase.ID, PRDeductionID, Heading1, year(CheckDate), NameBase.Number --ORDER BY NameBase.ID ORDER BY NameBase.Number

data.name: customSqlQuery6.Sql
data.value: SELECT B.*, C.RowNumber FROM (SELECT 'Deduction' As Type ,NameBase.ID As Employee_NameBaseID ,PRDeductionID as TypeID ,PRD.Title ,Sum(DeductionAmount) as DeductionAmount ,PRDH.CompanyID FROM PRDeductionHistory PRDH INNER JOIN PRDeduction PRD ON PRDH.PRDeductionID = PRD.ID and PRDH.CompanyID = PRD.CompanyID INNER JOIN PRPaycheckHistory PRP ON PRDH.PRPaycheckHistoryID = PRP.PRPaycheckHistoryID and PRDH.CompanyID = PRP.CompanyID INNER JOIN PREmployee ON PREmployee.PREmployeeID = PRP.EmployeeID and PREmployee.CompanyID = PRP.CompanyID INNER JOIN NameBase ON NameBase.ID = PREmployee.Employee_NameBaseID and PREmployee.CompanyID = @plngCompanyID --WHERE CheckDate BETWEEN DATEFROMPARTS(YEAR(@pdteCheckDate), 1, 1) AND DATEFROMPARTS(YEAR(@pdteCheckDate), 12,31) AND PRDeductionID NOT BETWEEN 12 AND 15 --Don't want Fica, Medi, SIT, or FIT WHERE CheckDate BETWEEN DATEFROMPARTS(YEAR(@pdteCheckDate), 1, 1) AND DATEFROMPARTS(YEAR(@pdteCheckDate), 12,31) AND PRD.DeductionCode NOT IN ('1','2','3','4') -- we cannot hard code PRDeductionID since it will be different in different databases user defined database. (BN) GROUP BY NameBase.ID, PRDeductionID, PRD.Title, PRDH.CompanyID UNION ALL SELECT 'Allowance' As Type ,NameBase.ID ,PRAH.PRAllowanceID ,PRA.Title ,Sum(AllowanceAmount) as AllowanceAmount ,PRAH.CompanyID FROM PRAllowanceHistory PRAH INNER JOIN PRAllowance PRA ON PRAH.PRAllowanceID = PRA.PRAllowanceID and PRAH.CompanyID = PRA.CompanyID INNER JOIN PRPaycheckHistory PRP ON PRAH.PRPaycheckHistoryID = PRP.PRPaycheckHistoryID and PRAH.CompanyID = PRP.CompanyID INNER JOIN PREmployee ON PREmployee.PREmployeeID = PRP.EmployeeID and PREmployee.CompanyID = PRP.CompanyID INNER JOIN NameBase ON NameBase.ID = PREmployee.Employee_NameBaseID and PREmployee.CompanyID = @plngCompanyID WHERE CheckDate BETWEEN DATEFROMPARTS(YEAR(@pdteCheckDate), 1, 1) AND DATEFROMPARTS(YEAR(@pdteCheckDate), 12,31) GROUP BY NameBase.ID, PRAH.PRAllowanceID, PRA.Title, PRAH.CompanyID) as B INNER JOIN (SELECT *, ROW_NUMBER() OVER(ORDER BY Type) RowNumber FROM( SELECT DISTINCT 'Deduction' As Type ,PRDeductionID as TypeID ,PRDH.CompanyID FROM PRDeductionHistory PRDH INNER JOIN PRDeduction PRD ON PRDH.PRDeductionID = PRD.ID and PRDH.CompanyID = PRD.CompanyID INNER JOIN PRPaycheckHistory PRP ON PRDH.PRPaycheckHistoryID = PRP.PRPaycheckHistoryID and PRDH.CompanyID = PRP.CompanyID INNER JOIN PREmployee ON PREmployee.PREmployeeID = PRP.EmployeeID and PREmployee.CompanyID = PRP.CompanyID INNER JOIN NameBase ON NameBase.ID = PREmployee.Employee_NameBaseID and PREmployee.CompanyID = @plngCompanyID --WHERE CheckDate BETWEEN DATEFROMPARTS(YEAR(@pdteCheckDate), 1, 1) AND DATEFROMPARTS(YEAR(@pdteCheckDate), 12,31) AND PRDeductionID NOT BETWEEN 12 AND 15 --Don't want Fica, Medi, SIT, or FIT WHERE CheckDate BETWEEN DATEFROMPARTS(YEAR(@pdteCheckDate), 1, 1) AND DATEFROMPARTS(YEAR(@pdteCheckDate), 12,31) AND PRD.DeductionCode NOT IN ('1','2','3','4') -- we cannot hard code PRDeductionID since it will be different in different databases user defined database. (BN) GROUP BY NameBase.ID, PRDeductionID, PRD.Title, PRDH.CompanyID UNION ALL SELECT DISTINCT 'Allowance' As Type ,PRAH.PRAllowanceID ,PRAH.CompanyID FROM PRAllowanceHistory PRAH INNER JOIN PRAllowance PRA ON PRAH.PRAllowanceID = PRA.PRAllowanceID and PRAH.CompanyID = PRA.CompanyID INNER JOIN PRPaycheckHistory PRP ON PRAH.PRPaycheckHistoryID = PRP.PRPaycheckHistoryID and PRAH.CompanyID = PRP.CompanyID INNER JOIN PREmployee ON PREmployee.PREmployeeID = PRP.EmployeeID and PREmployee.CompanyID = PRP.CompanyID INNER JOIN NameBase ON NameBase.ID = PREmployee.Employee_NameBaseID and PREmployee.CompanyID = @plngCompanyID WHERE CheckDate BETWEEN DATEFROMPARTS(YEAR(@pdteCheckDate), 1, 1) AND DATEFROMPARTS(YEAR(@pdteCheckDate), 12,31) GROUP BY NameBase.ID, PRAH.PRAllowanceID, PRA.Title,PRAH.CompanyID) a ) AS C ON B.Type = C.Type AND B.TypeID = C.TypeID ORDER By RowNumber
